Except, if you are basically a community initiative with an NGO for women and children. You cannot commercialize crayfish apart from this. St. Vincent and the Grenadines is one of the most heaven like islands in the Caribbean. People are envious of our environment and climate.

We have cannons on the ground that produce green energy. United States of America is also envious, this is not the topic we are making, what I am making is telling the Grenadines community that we have something to export that can match the affordability and the nature of Amazon, because one important issue is that it is well packed and can be manufactured in very different shapes, sizes , forms and colors. And then you can open up the export opportunities right away as it has to do with environmental issues, the best part.
